SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3259
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE FALKNER.
6668H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To repeal section 537.130, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to
unlawful or riotous assemblages.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Section 537.130, RSMo, is repealed and one new section enacted in lieu
2 thereof, to be known as section 537.130, to read as follows:
537.130. Any person or persons forming, directing, advising, encouraging, or
2 solicitinga part of an unlawful or riotous assemblage shall be jointly and severallyliable for
3 any damage to person or property caused by the acts of such assemblage, or of any person or
4 persons unlawfully connected therewith. As used in this section, "person or persons"
5 includes organizers and sponsors of an unlawful or riotous assemblage.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

